The paper proposes a framework for domain adaptation, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on marginalized domain adaptation, which involves adapting a model from a source domain to a target domain where the target domain has a different marginal distribution. This problem is relevant to several subfields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and statistical learning (cs.SD). Given that the paper deals with both image and text datasets, it is likely to be relevant to multiple subfields.
